Scotland's independent schools maintain a school record of excellence. This trend continued in 2018 with excellent new exam results enhanced by collective and individual success in sports, art, music and other community activities.
With more than 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS) seek to provide the highest level of service to students and their parents.
Independent schools are working to prepare their students for higher education, their chosen career and their place as citizens of the world.
As an education sector capable of designing and implementing a school curriculum on measurement, we note that contemporary languages remain popular and desirable in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a man in a language he understands, you speak to his head.
