And now, a page of our Almanach "Sunday Morning": On September 30, 1882, 136 years ago today, and THE COMPTEUR TOURNE... was born the future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger, in Germany.
Geiger has developed a method to detect and measure radioactivity; an invention that subsequently gave birth to the device known as Geiger counter.
