The European team won the Ryder Cup 2018 by beating the US team with a final score of 16.5 to 10.5 at the National Golf near Paris, France.
The United States has now lost six times on European soil and has not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe recovered the title when the Danish captain Thomas Bjorn's team crossed the 14.5-point bar to beat the United States.
The American star Phil Mickelson, who found himself in difficulty during most of the tournament, pushed his starting blow into the water at the 16th hole in par-3, giving his duel to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari has excelled in all his rounds, becoming one of the four players who has never reached 5-0-0 since the current format of the tournament, the first edition of which dates back to 1979.
